      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians view the UN's effectiveness in preventing major 21st-century wars as a qualified failure, though it has prevented numerous localized conflicts from escalating. The Security Council's structure, particularly the veto power held by permanent members, consistently paralyzes decisive action when great power interests clash. Therefore, while the UN manages crises, it demonstrably lacks the enforcement power to stop conflicts rooted in geopolitical rivalry.",
